# Internal Package Rules

## Package Access
- Classes in internal package must be package-private or protected
- Never use public access modifiers in internal package
- Internal classes only accessible within same module
- Use @Component, @Service, @Repository annotations appropriately

## Entity Rules  
- JPA entities must be in internal package
- Use proper JPA annotations (@Entity, @Id, @GeneratedValue)
- Include audit fields (createdAt, updatedAt) where appropriate
- Keep entities focused on data structure, minimal business logic

## Service Rules
- Internal services handle all business logic
- Services should be transactional where appropriate
- Return internal DTOs that facades convert to public records
- Handle domain events and validation logic

## Repository Rules
- Extend appropriate Spring Data repository interfaces
- Use JPA derived queries when possible
- Custom queries should use @Query annotation
- Focus on data access only, no business logic


